            '<p>Mr Manish Gupta was delighted to speak with a mentor of Solidarity, Mr Anurag Surana who is a deep domain expert in Specialty Chemicals. With over 35 years experience and a part of the core team that built PI Industries.  He is also the Chairman of 2 Specialty Chemical companies in India.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The conversation with him covered many topics</p>\n\n\n\n<ol start="1" style="list-style-type:lower-alpha" class="wp-block-list">\n<li>How Indian Specialty Chemicals companies have evolved over the last 20 years and expected trajectory</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Why most Indian companies should not be severely impacted by US tariffs</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Variables to look out for and questions to ask management teams when gauging whether companies are becoming better Assets</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Mistakes made by long term investors when they obsess over metrics like ROCE without making adjustments for the long gestation investments management teams are making. </li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Watch the full interview  <strong><a href="https://youtu.be/MaWtOm8jdSw?si=_S_EAmwAgvc8GM7Z" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">here</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>',
